The last few weeks have been a complete whirlwind and dream. When @tinsleymerrillpaul asked us to help bring @supportherstory Gallery to life, we didn’t hesitate. In just a few short weeks we (with the help of an incredible team of women), transformed a space in Sundance Square, Fort Worth into an exhibition of wearable art, designed by women around the globe. We couldn’t be more proud to be a part of this incredible project and movement. Congratulations, Tinsley!
It’s all fun and games until the Sunday Scaries hit! A fun game table moment from our Bridgehampton project. Photo: @patrickclinephotography

Today is the big day! I couldn’t be more excited to announce my hardware collection with @sa_baxter  This has been such a dream of mine and I am thrilled with how the George Suite turned out! Hope you all love it as much as I do!

Thank you for the outpouring of love and support yesterday! I’m so grateful to each and every one of you. I wanted to take y’all on a little behind the scenes of the collection. I first had the idea because I couldn’t find anything on the market for my own home and wanted to create something special that would speak to the history of the town of Washington. I started digging around and found a commemorative button from George Washington’s uniform that was worn at the Battle of Washington. It was a perfect motif for the face of the door knob. For the side profile I knew I wanted to pay homage to the orders of architecture since I have a lot of neoclassical elements in my home. Therefore we designed a deep fluted, columnesque side profile that in the lever style looks exactly like a column! A huge thank you to @sa_baxter for believing in me and making my vision come to life! Without you, there wouldn’t be the George Suite! Up next: installation photos in my home! PS- each piece is unique and is cast separately using its own mold. Truly one of a kind!

It’s Thursday and 5 o’clock somewhere! JHD is serving up Strawberry Mint Smashes in our favorite @halfpastsevenhome Olive Rocks Glasses. See below for the recipe. Cheers!
Ingredients:
- 4-5 ripe strawberries sliced in half
- 1 teaspoon honey, adjust to taste
- 5-7 mint leaves
- juice of half a lime
- 1 oz vodka
- seltzer or club soda to taste
- ice
- lime
- strawberries and mint for garnish
